articles.title: Afghanistan earthquake: At least 120 killed and 1,000 injured in 6.3 quake - BBC.com
articles.description: The 6.3 magnitude quake struck about 40km from the western city of Herat on Saturday morning.
articles.content:
Hundreds of people are feared dead and at least 1,000 are injured after a powerful earthquake hit western Afghanistan, near the Iranian border.
